You have logged an opportunity and must submit the attached Conflict Clearance Request Form (at the appropriate time if conflict clearance is required under the firm’s conflict clearance procedures Conflicts of Interest Management Procedures for Private Side Businesses within the South African Corporate and Investment Banking Business of Barclays Africa).
 
Please note that with effect from Monday, 30th of September 2013, the coverage that was previously provided by Absa Capital Compliance Control Room is now being provided by the Barclays Corporate and Investment Banking Compliance Control Room (“CIB Compliance Control Room”) and the Barclays Conflicts Management team within Compliance (“Conflicts Management”).  
 
Please submit the attached Conflict Clearance Request Form to Conflicts Management via Barclays South Africa Conflict Checks to apply for conflict clearance of your opportunity.   
 
Please also be reminded to keep CIB Compliance Control Room informed via Compliance Control Room London of material updates to the deal, including (but not limited to) receipt of material non public information, deal team additions, timing, mandate and announcements. 
 
It is important to be aware of the new contact details since Monday, 30th of September 2013.  The Abcap Control Room mailbox will no longer be operational and will be replaced by the below mailboxes:  
 
EMEA CIB Compliance Control Room (primary contact for all Control Room enquiries and transaction updates)
Email: Compliance Control Room London
Hotline: +44 20 777 33060 
 
EMEA Conflicts Management (primary contact for all conflict clearance requests)
Email: Barclays South Africa Conflict Checks
 
All notifications to Control Room / Conflicts Management should be via email, updates to CRM will not constitute valid Compliance notification.

